modules.description: This module provides functions to access and manipulate DSSI plugin descriptors, including retrieving API versions, associated LADSPA descriptors, and configuring instances. It supports operations for managing programs, MIDI controllers, and running synthesizer instances with precise event handling. Concrete use cases include loading and switching synthesizer programs, handling MIDI input, and executing multiple synths concurrently with event arrays.

Handles dynamic loading and unloading of DSSI plugins using shared library paths. Works with plugin handles represented by the abstract type `t`. Used to instantiate and release plugins at runtime, enabling integration of software synthesizers and effects.

Handles real-time audio synthesis and MIDI event processing through DSSI plugins. Provides initialization, plugin management, and descriptor manipulation for software synthesizers. Used to load plugins, switch programs, process MIDI events, and run multiple synthesizer instances concurrently with low-level event arrays.
